snippet.textDisplay:
The editing and visuals look great - Something that Lucas Film has never failed us with.


However - You have a big issue with "Diversity" - It seems like the employees in that room are far over-representing a minority of the population. Words like "diversity" are well-known Orwellian 'newspeak' for a particular political view.


Star wars would do far better with a panel of Mothers and Fathers with their kids - dreaming up an exciting world for the future of Star Wars.


As a long time fan of the Star Wars series, reading whats on that board, and seeing the very particularly selected "diverse" employees that are deciding on the future of this franchise, I'm already out. I'm not buying anything to do with this series, not because I'm against people choosing whatever lifestyle they want, I'm just sick of going to a movie, and instead of just getting to enjoy the plot-line and story, I'm getting lectured by a bunch of Hollywood people. I've no interest of going to work and working, then going out to a film and getting re-educated because the people who wrote a film think I'm homophobic or whatever else they want to call the rest of society.


Thank you Kathleen, but no thank you. Good luck
